, {\"ngram\": \"action\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1359}, {\"ngram\": \"the Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines boards\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1399}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The fight for gold should see the most powerful and explosive men's cyclists on the planet battle out for top spot, with big stares on the start line, track stands, and should-to-shoulder racing all commonplace in one of track's most exciting events.\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1652, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The fight\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1411}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1420}, {\"ngram\": \"the most powerful and explosive men's cyclists\", \"from\": 1432, \"to\": 1478}, {\"ngram\": \"the planet battle\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1499}, {\"ngram\": \"top spot\", \"from\": 1508, \"to\": 1516}, {\"ngram\": \"big stares\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1533}, {\"ngram\": \"the start line\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1551}, {\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1558}, {\"ngram\": \"shoulder\", \"from\": 1581, \"to\": 1589}, {\"ngram\": \"track's most exciting events\", \"from\": 1623, \"to\": 1651}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Track sprinting has long featured in the Olympics for men, with the first appearance coming in the inaugural modern incarnation of the Games in Athens 1896.\", \"from\": 1654, \"to\": 1810, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1798, \"end\": 1804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999868123, \"rank\": 1.3151348431014778e-11, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Track sprinting\", \"from\": 1654, \"to\": 1669}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1691, \"to\": 1703}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 1708, \"to\": 1711}, {\"ngram\": \"the first appearance\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1738}, {\"ngram\": \"the inaugural modern incarnation\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1781}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 1794}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 will be the 22 different Olympic champions being decided in that time.\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1892, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1811, \"end\": 1821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.8802940975132436e-23, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 22 different Olympic champions\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1864}, {\"ngram\": \"that time\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 1891}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the Brits dominated the dash for gold between Beijing 2008 and Rio 2016, the tide has turned in recent years to the Dutch being producing the riders to beat, mainly through five-time World and defending Olympic Champion Harrie Lavreysen, who has commanded the last six years of track sprinting.\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 2194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2016, \"end\": 2021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9984230022708487, \"rank\": 0.0013546764446705016, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 2120, \"end\": 2136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Harrie Lavreysen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Brits\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 1909}, {\"ngram\": \"the dash\", \"from\": 1920, \"to\": 1928}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 1937}, {\"ngram\": \"Beijing\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 1953}